# Example Camera Parameters for MOIL Fisheye Dewarping
# Save this file to: asset/parameter_camera/custom.txt

# Polynomial coefficients for radial distortion correction
# PARA p0 p1 p2 p3 p4 p5
PARA 0.0 0.0 -35.475 73.455 -41.392 499.33

# Original image dimensions
ORG_W 2592.0
ORG_H 1944.0

# Optical center coordinates (image center point)
ORG_ICX 1296.0
ORG_ICY 972.0

# How to obtain these values:
# 1. Use MOIL calibration software with checkerboard pattern
# 2. Or contact your fisheye camera manufacturer for parameters
# 3. Adjust ORG_ICX and ORG_ICY if optical center is not at image center
